  "texts": [
    "Delayed exposure to language can hinder their early social and cognitive development.",
    "Concurrently, children of deaf adults (CODAs) are exposed to sign language from an early age but may experience delayed spoken language development.",
    "This delay can lead to social challenges, such as bullying, affecting their self-confidence and even long-term physical and psychological development.",
    "Furthermore, parents of deaf children (PODCs) may find learning sign language daunting due to time restrictions and the lack of structured learning opportunities, impacting both CODAs and deaf children face continued communication challenges at home.",
    "A recent report 4 indicates that most PODCs fail to use sign language in communication with deaf children."
  ],
